---
id: org.dxos.worker-framework
name: WorkerFramework
version: 0.10.0
---

Generic worker management framework for DXOS client services. This spec captures
the package's namespace modules and their public API.

Modules follow the DXOS namespace-module styleguide: PascalCase file in `src/`,
marked `// @import-as-namespace`, re-exported from `index.ts` as
`export * as <Name> from './<Name>'`, and consumed by callers as a namespace
(`RpcTiming.serverLayer`, never a bare `rpcTimingServerLayer`).

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.

| Term     | URI                          |
|----------|------------------------------|
| `module` | `org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0`    |

## Modules

```mdl
module RpcTiming
  desc: |
    Effect RPC middleware that measures per-request queue-wait and service time
    across the worker boundary. The client stamps a send timestamp header; the
    server derives queue-wait from it, times the handler, records samples in a
    bounded ring buffer, and logs slow requests.
  api:
    # Constants
    SENT_AT_HEADER: string                # cross-thread send-time header ('x-dxos-rpc-sent-at').

    # Types
    Options: { minLogMs?: number }        # min queue-wait / service ms before logging (default 100).
    MetadataService: {...}                # per-request timing: sentAt?, dispatchedAt, queueWaitMs?, serviceMs?.
    Sample: {...}                         # one recorded RPC: tag, queueWaitMs?, serviceMs, at.
    StatsSnapshot: {...}                  # samples[] + maxQueueWaitMs + maxServiceMs.

    # Effect tags
    Metadata: Context.Tag                 # request-scoped MetadataService tag.
    Middleware: RpcMiddleware.Tag         # wrap middleware; provides Metadata; requiredForClient.

    # Group wiring
    applyMiddleware: (group) => group     # attaches Middleware to every RPC; idempotent.
    serverLayer: (options?) => Layer      # derives queue-wait + service time, records + logs.
    clientLayer: () => Layer              # stamps SENT_AT_HEADER on outbound RPCs.

    # Stats collection
    recordSample: (Sample) => void        # append one completed RPC (ring buffer, max 100).
    getStatsSnapshot: () => StatsSnapshot  # snapshot of samples from the server middleware.
    resetStats: () => void                # clear collected samples (tests).

    # Option helpers (consumed by the sibling Rpc module)
    isEnabled: (timing?) => boolean       # whether timing is on for a serve/client options bag.
    resolveOptions: (timing?) => Options  # normalize boolean | Options to an Options bag.
```

`RpcTiming` currently lives in `src/internal/rpc-timing.ts` with `RpcTiming`-prefixed,
directly-exported symbols. The target is a single `src/RpcTiming.ts` namespace module;
the api above is the post-rename (unprefixed) surface. The restyle renames the current
symbols to their unprefixed namespace members:

| Current (`src/internal/rpc-timing.ts`) | Target (`RpcTiming.*`) |
|----------------------------------------|------------------------|
| `RPC_TIMING_SENT_AT_HEADER`            | `SENT_AT_HEADER`       |
| `RpcTimingOptions`                     | `Options`              |
| `RpcTimingMetadataService`             | `MetadataService`      |
| `RpcTimingSample`                      | `Sample`               |
| `RpcTimingStatsSnapshot`               | `StatsSnapshot`        |
| `RpcTimingMetadata`                    | `Metadata`             |
| `RpcTimingMiddleware`                  | `Middleware`           |
| `applyRpcTimingMiddleware`             | `applyMiddleware`      |
| `rpcTimingServerLayer`                 | `serverLayer`          |
| `rpcTimingClientLayer`                 | `clientLayer`          |
| `recordRpcTimingSample`                | `recordSample`         |
| `getRpcTimingStatsSnapshot`            | `getStatsSnapshot`     |
| `resetRpcTimingStats`                  | `resetStats`           |
| `isRpcTimingEnabled`                   | `isEnabled`            |
| `resolveRpcTimingOptions`              | `resolveOptions`       |

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

```mdl
ext module
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.module@1.0
  desc: |
    An ESM namespace module following the DXOS namespace-module styleguide:
    PascalCase file in src/, marked `// @import-as-namespace`, and re-exported
    from index.ts as `export * as <Name> from './<Name>'`. Callers import it as a
    namespace, so members are unprefixed (`RpcTiming.Options`, not `RpcTimingOptions`).
    The file path is inferred from the block name (`RpcTiming` → `src/RpcTiming.ts`).
    The full rules live in the styleguide referenced below rather than inline here.
  styleguide: ../../../docs/style/namespace-modules.md
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    api: ApiMap         # public members reached as `<Name>.<member>`  (name: TypeExpr # comment)
```
